Articles.Content:
After playing KSP happily last year, I finally decided to return to the game.  Unfortunately, when I turned on my laptop for the first time in ages,  I forgot that steam auto runs and started updating to the latest version of the game.  The new version is being a total nightmare.  The game crashes constantly and now wont show any saved games at all (not even ones created in the new version)

Is there anyway / anywhere I can download an older version of the game (last version I played, which was stable, was the one that introduced cargo bays with ramps). I was playing on a marginal laptop, but the old version worked well with the graphics turned down low.  Now the game is broken for me which, as you can imagine, is Really frustrating.

Any advice / tips much appreciated

Regards

Clipperride.

Saves - when I try and resume a saved game the dialogue box opens but does not list any games. I've tried creating a new game, saving it, quitting to main screen - but it still doesn't appear when I try and reload it.

Logs - Some crashes have generated a log (I'll try and post one when I'm back on the laptop) but it usually gives a blue screen error and Windows (7) restarts.  

When KSP first updated, I could play for an hour or so, completing several flights) without before crashing.  Now it seems as soon as I splash down in the sea, return to the capsule after an EVA or try and recover the vessel after touching down on land, it will crash.

One other thing I've noticed is that during any of the above, the laptop will switch between the home screen and the game a couple of times before either continuing or crashing.

I've tried, through Steam, deleting local files and redownloading the game, which worked for a while before crashing all the time again.

I'd really love to play the game again to take my mind off an upcoming hospital stay, but end up more wound up than before!

 

PS looking at my previous posts, the version I had that worked just fine was from October 2015.  Anyway of getting a copy of that version?

Edited August 15, 2016 by Clipperride
Additional info

PS I know the saved games are still there somewhere as, when I tried creating a new game, using the same name as a previous save, the warning about overwriting the original appears.  

It's strange as, despite crashing a lot, I could reload the game.  The save game list has disappeared without any changes to the game or settings.

Hope someone has some suggestions as I just want my KSP fix!

Cheers

Hi @Clipperride, the crash log is actually rather unhelpful, sorry

The files that will tell us the most are the KSP.log in the Kerbal Space Program folder and the output_log.txt in KSP_Data.

If you also run dxdiag from the start menu and save the hardware report that will help too.

You could put these on dropbox.com or post them here in spoiler tags, using the eye button on the editor.

Thank you for the advice and here (I hope) is the info you asked for

Just to summarise the solution for anyone reading this with the same issues.

1) The repeated crashes caused by entering the capsule after EVA was a mix of limited memory and out dated drivers. FIX = updating the system using the Steam driver check and my laptop's (HP) own tune-up utility. Then I dedicated a memory stick using Windows Ready Boost to add some extra RAM.

2} Empty "Resume Saved Game" dialogue box. FIX = checked for a corrupt saved game (which explains why this second issue appeared later than the first). The solution was given by @sal_vager in another thread, which I have copied below

"It sounds like one of your saves is corrupt, when this happens none will show.

Check that all saves have a persistent.sfs, you may have to copy the quicksave.sfs and rename it if the persistent.sfs is missing.

Also check that all saves have a ships folder with a VAB and SPH folder, you may have to make the appropriate folder if these are missing.

If this doesn't help, remove each folder one at a time until the saves start working again.

The training and scenarios folders are stock KSP folders and should not be removed.

Hope this helps!" - answer by sal_vager.
